Results of sequencing showed a high level of conservation amongst the Queensland KIV sequences as well as between the Queensland and Swedish sequences with 99.4–100% similarity at a nucleotide level (Fig. 1
). However these observations are limited by the small number of specimens examined in each study. One genome sequence derived from an NPA collected from a 6-month-old Queensland boy showed a 10 bp insertion at position 60–69 of the KIV genome (Table 3
), suggesting that variable regions of the KIV genome may occur.
